{"nodes":[{"content":"Deploy Windows 10 in a school (Windows 10)","pos":[11,53]},{"content":"Learn how to integrate your school environment with Microsoft Office 365, Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS), and Microsoft Azure Active Directory (Azure AD).","pos":[67,231]},{"content":"Deploy Windows 10 and apps to new devices or upgrade existing devices to Windows 10.","pos":[232,316]},{"content":"Manage faculty, students, and devices by using Microsoft Intune and Group Policy.","pos":[317,398]},{"content":"Deploy Windows 10 in a school","pos":[622,651]},{"content":"Applies to","pos":[656,666]},{"content":"Windows 10","pos":[672,682]},{"content":"This guide shows you how to deploy the Windows 10 operating system in a school environment.","pos":[684,775]},{"content":"You learn how to deploy Windows 10 in classrooms; integrate the school environment with Microsoft Office 365, Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS), and Microsoft Azure Active Directory (Azure AD); and deploy Windows 10 and your apps to new devices or upgrade existing devices to Windows 10.","pos":[776,1070]},{"content":"This guide also describes how to use Microsoft Intune and Group Policy to manage devices.","pos":[1071,1160]},{"content":"Finally, the guide discusses common, ongoing maintenance tasks that you will perform after initial deployment as well as the automated tools and built-in features of the operating system.","pos":[1161,1348]},{"content":"Prepare for school deployment","pos":[1353,1382]},{"content":"Proper preparation is essential for a successful school deployment.","pos":[1384,1451]},{"content":"To avoid common mistakes, your first step is to plan a typical school configuration.","pos":[1452,1536]},{"content":"Just as with building a house, you need a blueprint for what your school should look like when it’s finished.","pos":[1537,1646]},{"content":"The second step in preparation is to learn how you will configure your school.","pos":[1647,1725]},{"content":"Just as a builder needs to have the right tools to build a house, you need the right set of tools to deploy your school.","pos":[1726,1846]},{"content":"Plan a typical school configuration","pos":[1852,1887]},{"content":"As part of preparing for your school deployment, you need to plan your configuration—the focus of this guide.","pos":[1889,1998]},{"content":"Figure 1 illustrates a typical finished school configuration that you can use as a model (the blueprint in our builder analogy) for the finished state.","pos":[1999,2150]},{"content":"fig 1","pos":[2154,2159]},{"content":"Figure 1.","pos":[2204,2213]},{"content":"Typical school configuration for this guide","pos":[2214,2257]},{"content":"Figure 2 shows the classroom configuration this guide uses.","pos":[2260,2319]},{"content":"fig 2","pos":[2323,2328]},{"content":"Figure 2.","pos":[2373,2382]},{"content":"Typical classroom configuration in a school","pos":[2383,2426]},{"content":"This school configuration has the following characteristics:","pos":[2429,2489]},{"content":"It contains one or more admin devices.","pos":[2492,2530]},{"content":"It contains two or more classrooms.","pos":[2533,2568]},{"content":"Each classroom contains one teacher device.","pos":[2571,2614]},{"content":"The classrooms connect to each other through multiple subnets.","pos":[2617,2679]},{"content":"All devices in each classroom connect to a single subnet.","pos":[2682,2739]},{"content":"All devices have high-speed, persistent connections to each other and to the Internet.","pos":[2742,2828]},{"content":"All teachers and students have access to Windows Store or Windows Store for Business.","pos":[2831,2916]},{"content":"All devices receive software updates from Intune (or another device management system).","pos":[2919,3006]},{"content":"You install a 64-bit version of Windows 10 on the admin device.","pos":[3009,3072]},{"content":"You install the Windows Assessment and Deployment Kit (Windows ADK) on the admin device.","pos":[3075,3163]},{"content":"You install the Windows Assessment and Deployment Kit (Windows ADK) on the admin device.","pos":[3166,3254]},{"content":"You install the 64-bit version of the Microsoft Deployment Toolkit (MDT) 2013 Update 2 on the admin device.","pos":[3257,3364]},{"pos":[3366,3473],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>In this guide, all references to MDT refer to the 64-bit version of MDT 2013 Update 2."},{"content":"The devices use Azure AD in Office 365 Education for identity management.","pos":[3476,3549]},{"content":"If you have on-premises AD DS, you can <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>integrate Azure AD with on-premises AD DS<ept id=\"p1\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/active-directory-aadconnect/)</ept>.","pos":[3552,3721]},{"pos":[3729,4115],"content":"Use <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Intune<ept id=\"p1\">](http://technet.microsoft.com/library/jj676587.aspx)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>compliance settings in Office 365<ept id=\"p2\">](https://support.office.com/en-us/article/Manage-mobile-devices-in-Office-365-dd892318-bc44-4eb1-af00-9db5430be3cd?ui=en-US&amp;rs=en-US&amp;ad=US)</ept>, or <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>Group Policy<ept id=\"p3\">](http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc725828%28v=ws.10%29.aspx?f=255&amp;MSPPError=-2147217396)</ept> in AD DS to manage devices."},{"content":"Each device supports a one-student-per-device or multiple-students-per-device scenario.","pos":[4118,4205]},{"content":"The devices can be a mixture of different make, model, and processor architecture (32 bit or 64 bit) or be identical.","pos":[4208,4325]},{"content":"To initiate Windows 10 deployment, use a USB flash drive, DVD-ROM or CD-ROM, or Pre-Boot Execution Environment Boot (PXE Boot).","pos":[4328,4455]},{"content":"The devices can be a mixture of different Windows 10 editions, such as Windows 10 Home, Windows 10 Pro, and Windows 10 Education.","pos":[4458,4587]},{"content":"Office 365 Education allows:","pos":[4589,4617]},{"content":"Students and faculty to use Microsoft Office Online to create and edit Microsoft Word, OneNote, PowerPoint, and Excel documents in a browser.","pos":[4621,4762]},{"pos":[4765,4900],"content":"Teachers to use the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>OneNote Class Notebook app<ept id=\"p1\">](https://www.onenote.com/classnotebook)</ept> to share content and collaborate with students."},{"pos":[4903,5058],"content":"Faculty to use the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>OneNote Staff Notebooks app<ept id=\"p1\">](https://www.onenote.com/staffnotebookedu)</ept> to collaborate with other teachers, administration, and faculty."},{"content":"Teachers to employ Sway to create interactive educational digital storytelling.","pos":[5061,5140]},{"content":"Students and faculty to use email and calendars, with mailboxes up to 50 GB per user.","pos":[5143,5228]},{"content":"Faculty to use advanced email features like email archiving and legal hold capabilities.","pos":[5231,5319]},{"content":"Faculty to help prevent unauthorized users from accessing documents and email by using Azure Rights Management.","pos":[5322,5433]},{"content":"Faculty to use advanced compliance tools on the unified eDiscovery pages in the Office 365 Compliance Center.","pos":[5436,5545]},{"content":"Faculty to host online classes, parent–teacher conferences, and other collaboration in Skype for Business or Skype.","pos":[5548,5663]},{"content":"Students and faculty to access up to 1 TB of personal cloud storage that users inside and outside the educational institution can share through OneDrive for Business.","pos":[5666,5832]},{"content":"Teachers to provide collaboration in the classroom through Microsoft SharePoint Online team sites.","pos":[5835,5933]},{"content":"Students and faculty to use Office 365 Video to manage videos.","pos":[5936,5998]},{"content":"Students and faculty to use Yammer to collaborate through private social networking.","pos":[6001,6085]},{"content":"Students and faculty to access classroom resources from anywhere on any device (including Windows 10 Mobile, iOS, and Android devices).","pos":[6088,6223]},{"pos":[6225,6366],"content":"For more information about Office 365 Education features and a FAQ, go to <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Office 365 Education<ept id=\"p1\">](https://products.office.com/en-us/academic)</ept>."},{"content":"How to configure a school","pos":[6371,6396]},{"content":"Now that you have the plan (blueprint) for your classroom, you’re ready to learn about the tools you will use to deploy it.","pos":[6398,6521]},{"content":"There are many tools you could use to accomplish the task, but this guide focuses on using those tools that require the least infrastructure and technical knowledge.","pos":[6522,6687]},{"content":"The primary tool you will use to deploy Windows 10 in your school is MDT, which uses Windows ADK components to make deployment easier.","pos":[6689,6823]},{"content":"You could just use the Windows ADK to perform your deployment, but MDT simplifies the process by providing an intuitive, wizard-driven user interface (UI).","pos":[6824,6979]},{"content":"You can use MDT as a stand-alone tool or integrate it with Microsoft System Center Configuration Manager.","pos":[6981,7086]},{"content":"As a stand-alone tool, MDT performs Lite Touch Installation (LTI) deployments—deployments that require minimal infrastructure and allow you to control the level of automation.","pos":[7087,7262]},{"content":"When integrated with System Center Configuration Manager, MDT performs Zero Touch Installation (ZTI) deployments, which require more infrastructure (such as System Center Configuration Manager) but result in fully automated deployments.","pos":[7263,7499]},{"content":"MDT includes the Deployment Workbench—a console from which you can manage the deployment of Windows 10 and your apps.","pos":[7501,7618]},{"content":"You configure the deployment process in the Deployment Workbench, including the management of operating systems, device drivers, apps and migration of user settings on existing devices.","pos":[7619,7804]},{"content":"LTI performs deployment from a <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>deployment share<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>—a network-shared folder on the device where you installed MDT.","pos":[7807,7919]},{"content":"You can perform over-the-network deployments from the deployment share or perform deployments from a local copy of the deployment share on a USB drive or DVD.","pos":[7920,8078]},{"content":"You will learn more about MDT in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Prepare the admin device<ept id=\"p1\">](#prepare-the-admin-device)</ept> section.","pos":[8079,8178]},{"content":"The focus of MDT is deployment, so you also need tools that help you manage your Windows 10 devices and apps.","pos":[8180,8289]},{"content":"You can manage Windows 10 devices and apps with Intune, the Compliance Management feature in Office 365, or Group Policy in AD DS.","pos":[8290,8420]},{"content":"You can use any combination of these tools based on your school requirements.","pos":[8421,8498]},{"content":"The configuration process requires the following devices:","pos":[8500,8557]},{"content":"Admin device.","pos":[8563,8576]},{"content":"This is the device you use for your day-to-day job functions.","pos":[8579,8640]},{"content":"It’s also the one you use to create and manage the Windows 10 and app deployment process.","pos":[8641,8730]},{"content":"You install the Windows ADK and MDT on this device.","pos":[8731,8782]},{"content":"Faculty devices.","pos":[8787,8803]},{"content":"These are the devices that the teachers and other faculty use for their day-to-day job functions.","pos":[8806,8903]},{"content":"You use the admin device to deploy (or upgrade) Windows 10 and apps to these devices.","pos":[8904,8989]},{"content":"Student devices.","pos":[8994,9010]},{"content":"The students will use these devices.","pos":[9013,9049]},{"content":"You will use the admin device deploy (or upgrade) Windows 10 and apps to them.","pos":[9050,9128]},{"content":"The high-level process for deploying and configuring devices within individual classrooms and the school as a whole is as follows and illustrated in Figure 3:","pos":[9130,9288]},{"content":"Prepare the admin device for use, which includes installing the Windows ADK and MDT.","pos":[9293,9377]},{"content":"On the admin device, create and configure the Office 365 Education subscription that you will use for each classroom in the school.","pos":[9381,9512]},{"content":"On the admin device, configure integration between on-premises AD DS and Azure AD (if you have an on premises AD DS configuration).","pos":[9516,9647]},{"content":"On the admin device, create and configure a Windows Store for Business portal.","pos":[9651,9729]},{"content":"On the admin device, prepare for management of the Windows 10 devices after deployment.","pos":[9733,9820]},{"content":"On the student and faculty devices, deploy Windows 10 to new or existing devices, or upgrade eligible devices to Windows 10.","pos":[9824,9948]},{"content":"On the admin device, manage the Windows 10 devices and apps, the Office 365 subscription, and the AD DS and Azure AD integration.","pos":[9952,10081]},{"content":"fig 3","pos":[10085,10090]},{"content":"Figure 3.","pos":[10135,10144]},{"content":"How school configuration works","pos":[10145,10175]},{"content":"Each of the steps illustrated in Figure 3 directly correspond to the remaining high-level sections in this guide.","pos":[10178,10291]},{"content":"Summary","pos":[10297,10304]},{"content":"In this section, you looked at the final configuration of your individual classrooms and the school as a whole upon completion of this guide.","pos":[10306,10447]},{"content":"You also learned the high-level steps you need to perform to deploy the faculty and student devices in your school.","pos":[10448,10563]},{"content":"Prepare the admin device","pos":[10568,10592]},{"content":"Now, you’re ready to prepare the admin device for use in the school.","pos":[10594,10662]},{"content":"This process includes installing the Windows ADK, installing the MDT, and creating the MDT deployment share.","pos":[10663,10771]},{"content":"Install the Windows ADK","pos":[10777,10800]},{"content":"The first step in preparing the admin device is to install the Windows ADK.","pos":[10802,10877]},{"content":"The Windows ADK contains the deployment tools that MDT uses, including the Windows Preinstallation Environment (Windows PE), the Windows User State Migration Tool (USMT), and Deployment Image Servicing and Management.","pos":[10878,11095]},{"content":"When you install the Windows ADK on the admin device, select the following features:","pos":[11097,11181]},{"content":"Deployment tools","pos":[11185,11201]},{"content":"Windows Preinstallation Environment (Windows PE)","pos":[11204,11252]},{"content":"User State Migration Tool (USMT)","pos":[11255,11287]},{"pos":[11289,11488],"content":"For more information about installing the Windows ADK, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Step 2-2: Install the Windows ADK<ept id=\"p1\">](http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn781086.aspx?f=255&amp;MSPPError=-2147217396#InstallWindowsADK)</ept>."},{"content":"Install MDT","pos":[11494,11505]},{"content":"Next, install MDT.","pos":[11507,11525]},{"content":"MDT uses the Windows ADK to help you manage and perform Windows 10 and app deployment and is a free tool available directly from Microsoft.","pos":[11526,11665]},{"content":"You can use MDT to deploy 32-bit or 64-bit versions of Windows 10.","pos":[11667,11733]},{"content":"Install the 64-bit version of MDT to support deployment of 32-bit and 64-bit operating systems.","pos":[11734,11829]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>If you install the 32-bit version of MDT, you can install only 32-bit versions of Windows 10.","pos":[11832,11946]},{"content":"Ensure that you download and install the 64-bit version of MDT so that you can install 64-bit and 32 bit versions of the operating system.","pos":[11947,12085]},{"pos":[12087,12276],"content":"For more information about installing MDT on the admin device, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Installing a New Instance of MDT<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn759415.aspx#InstallingaNewInstanceofMDT)</ept>."},{"content":"Now, you’re ready to create the MDT deployment share and populate it with the operating system, apps, and device drivers you want to deploy to your devices.","pos":[12278,12434]},{"content":"Create a deployment share","pos":[12440,12465]},{"content":"MDT includes the Deployment Workbench, a graphical user interface that you can use to manage MDT deployment shares.","pos":[12467,12582]},{"content":"A deployment share is a shared folder that contains all the MDT deployment content.","pos":[12583,12666]},{"content":"The LTI Deployment Wizard accesses the deployment content over the network or from a local copy of the deployment share (known as MDT deployment media).","pos":[12667,12819]},{"pos":[12821,13036],"content":"For more information about how to create a deployment share, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Step 3-1: Create an MDT Deployment Share<ept id=\"p1\">](http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn781086.aspx?f=255&amp;MSPPError=-2147217396#CreateMDTDeployShare)</ept>."},{"content":"Summary","pos":[13042,13049]},{"content":"In this section, you installed the Windows ADK and MDT on the admin device.","pos":[13051,13126]},{"content":"You also created the MDT deployment share that you will configure and use later in the LTI deployment process.","pos":[13127,13237]},{"content":"Create and configure Office 365","pos":[13242,13273]},{"content":"Office 365 is one of the core components of your classroom environment.","pos":[13275,13346]},{"content":"You create and manage student identities in Office 365, and students and teachers use the suite as their email, contacts, and calendar system.","pos":[13347,13489]},{"content":"Teachers and students use Office 365 collaboration features such as SharePoint, OneNote, and OneDrive for Business.","pos":[13490,13605]},{"content":"As a first step in deploying your classroom, create an Office 365 Education subscription, and then configure Office 365 for the classroom.","pos":[13607,13745]},{"content":"For more information about Office 365 Education deployment, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>School deployment of Office 365 Education<ept id=\"p1\">](http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/education/products/office-365-deployment-resources/default.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[13746,13950]},{"content":"Select the appropriate Office 365 Education license plan","pos":[13956,14012]},{"content":"Complete the following steps to select the appropriate Office 365 Education license plan for your school:","pos":[14014,14119]},{"content":"Determine the number of faculty members and students who will use the classroom.","pos":[14130,14210]},{"content":"Office 365 Education licensing plans are available specifically for faculty and students.","pos":[14215,14304]},{"content":"You must assign faculty and students the correct licensing plan.","pos":[14305,14369]},{"content":"Determine the faculty members and students who need to install Office applications on devices (if any).","pos":[14380,14483]},{"content":"Faculty and students can use Office applications online (standard plans) or run them locally (Office 365 ProPlus plans).","pos":[14484,14604]},{"content":"Table 1 lists the advantages and disadvantages of standard and Office 365 ProPlus plans.","pos":[14605,14693]},{"content":"Table 1.","pos":[14706,14714]},{"content":"Comparison of standard and Microsoft Office 365 ProPlus plans","pos":[14715,14776]},{"content":"Plan","pos":[14914,14918]},{"content":"Advantages","pos":[14941,14951]},{"content":"Disadvantages","pos":[14974,14987]},{"content":"Standard","pos":[15024,15032]},{"content":"Less expensive than Office 365 ProPlus","pos":[15049,15087]},{"content":"Can be run from any device","pos":[15096,15122]},{"content":"No installation necessary","pos":[15131,15156]},{"content":"Must have an Internet connection to use it","pos":[15183,15225]},{"content":"Does not support all the features found in Office 365 ProPlus","pos":[15234,15295]},{"content":"Office ProPlus","pos":[15324,15338]},{"content":"Only requires an Internet connection every 30 days (for activation)","pos":[15355,15422]},{"content":"Supports full set of Office features","pos":[15431,15467]},{"content":"Requires installation","pos":[15494,15515]},{"content":"Can be installed on only five devices per user (there is no limit to the number of devices on which you can run Office apps online)","pos":[15524,15655]},{"content":"The best user experience is to run Office 365 ProPlus or use native Office apps on mobile devices.","pos":[15701,15799]},{"content":"If neither of these options is available, use Office applications online.","pos":[15800,15873]},{"content":"In addition, all Office 365 plans provide a better user experience by storing documents in OneDrive for Business, which is included in all Office 365 plans.","pos":[15874,16030]},{"content":"OneDrive for Business keeps content in sync among devices and helps ensure that users always have access to their documents on any device.","pos":[16031,16169]},{"content":"Determine whether students or faculty need Azure Rights Management.","pos":[16180,16247]},{"content":"You can use Azure Rights Management to protect classroom information against unauthorized access.","pos":[16252,16349]},{"content":"Azure Rights Management protects your information inside or outside the classroom through encryption, identity, and authorization policies, securing your files and email.","pos":[16350,16520]},{"content":"You can retain control of the information, even when it’s shared with people outside the classroom or your educational institution.","pos":[16521,16652]},{"content":"Azure Rights Management is free to use with all Office 365 Education license plans.","pos":[16653,16736]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure Rights Management<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/jj585024.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[16737,16842]},{"content":"Record the Office 365 Education license plans needed for the classroom in Table 2.","pos":[16852,16934]},{"content":"Table 2.","pos":[16947,16955]},{"content":"Office 365 Education license plans needed for the classroom","pos":[16956,17015]},{"content":"Quantity","pos":[17136,17144]},{"content":"Plan","pos":[17167,17171]},{"content":"Office 365 Education for students","pos":[17217,17250]},{"content":"Office 365 Education for faculty","pos":[17278,17310]},{"content":"Azure Rights Management for students","pos":[17338,17374]},{"content":"Azure Rights Management for faculty","pos":[17402,17437]},{"content":"You will use the Office 365 Education license plan information you record in Table 2 in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create user accounts in Office 365<ept id=\"p1\">](#create-user-accounts-in-office-365)</ept> section of this guide.","pos":[17472,17660]},{"content":"Create a new Office 365 Education subscription","pos":[17676,17722]},{"content":"To create a new Office 365 Education subscription for use in the classroom, use your educational institution’s email account.","pos":[17724,17849]},{"content":"There are no costs to you or to students for signing up for Office 365 Education subscriptions.","pos":[17850,17945]},{"pos":[17948,18149],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>If you already have an Office 365 Education subscription, you can use that subscription and continue to the next section, <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Add domains and subdomains<ept id=\"p2\">](#add-domains-and-subdomains)</ept>."},{"content":"To create a new Office 365 subscription","pos":[18156,18195]},{"pos":[18200,18310],"content":"In Microsoft Edge or Internet Explorer, type <ph id=\"ph1\">`https://portal.office.com/start?sku=faculty`</ph> in the address bar."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>If you have already used your current sign-in account to create a new Office 365 subscription, you will be prompted to sign in.","pos":[18319,18466]},{"content":"If you want to create a new Office 365 subscription, start an In-Private Window in one of the following:","pos":[18467,18571]},{"pos":[18581,18755],"content":"Microsoft Edge by opening the Microsoft Edge app, either pressing Ctrl+Shift+P or clicking or tapping <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>More actions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, and then clicking or tapping <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>New InPrivate window<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>."},{"pos":[18760,18964],"content":"Internet Explorer 11 by opening Internet Explorer 11, either pressing Ctrl+Shift+P or clicking or tapping <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, clicking or tapping <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Safety<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, and then clicking or tapping <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>InPrivate Browsing<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>."},{"content":"On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Get started<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, type your school email address in the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Enter your school email address<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> box, and then click <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Sign up<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>.","pos":[18971,19106]},{"content":"You will receive an email in your school email account.","pos":[19107,19162]},{"content":"Click the hyperlink in the email in your school email account.","pos":[19166,19228]},{"content":"On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>One last thing<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, complete your user information, and then click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Start<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[19232,19321]},{"content":"The wizard creates your new Office 365 Education subscription, and you are automatically signed in as the administrative user you specified when you created the subscription.","pos":[19322,19496]},{"content":"Add domains and subdomains","pos":[19502,19528]},{"content":"Now that you have created your new Office 365 Education subscription, add the domains and subdomains that your institution uses.","pos":[19530,19658]},{"content":"For example, if your institution has contoso.edu as the primary domain name but you have subdomains for students or faculty (such as students.contoso.edu and faculty.contoso.edu), then you need to add the subdomains.","pos":[19659,19875]},{"content":"To add additional domains and subdomains","pos":[19882,19922]},{"pos":[19927,19995],"content":"In the Office 365 admin center, in the list view, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>DOMAINS<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>."},{"pos":[19999,20085],"content":"In the details pane, above the list of domains, on the menu bar, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Add domain<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>."},{"pos":[20089,20201],"content":"In the Add a New Domain in Office 365 Wizard, on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Verify domain wizard<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Let’s get started<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>."},{"pos":[20205,20337],"content":"On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Verify domain<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> wizard page, in the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Enter a domain you already own<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> box, type your domain name, and then click <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Next<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>."},{"content":"Sign in to your domain name management provider (for example, Network Solutions or GoDaddy), and then complete the steps for your provider.","pos":[20341,20480]},{"content":"Repeat these steps for each domain and subdomain you want faculty and students to use for your institution.","pos":[20484,20591]},{"content":"Configure automatic tenant join","pos":[20597,20628]},{"content":"To make it easier for faculty and students to join your Office 365 Education subscription (or <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>tenant<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>), allow them to automatically sign up to your tenant (<bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>automatic tenant join<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>).","pos":[20630,20812]},{"content":"In automatic tenant join, when a faculty member or student signs up for Office 365, Office 365 automatically adds (joins) the user to your Office 365 tenant.","pos":[20813,20970]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>By default, automatic tenant join is enabled in Office 365 Education, with the exception of certain areas in Europe, the Middle East, and Africa.","pos":[20973,21139]},{"content":"These countries require opt-in steps to add new users to existing Office 365 tenants.","pos":[21140,21225]},{"content":"Check your country requirements to determine the automatic tenant join default configuration.","pos":[21226,21319]},{"content":"Also, if you use Azure AD Connect, then automatic tenant join is disabled.","pos":[21320,21394]},{"content":"Office 365 uses the domain portion of the user’s email address to know which Office 365 tenant to join.","pos":[21396,21499]},{"content":"For example, if a faculty member or student provides an email address of user@contoso.edu, then Office 365 automatically performs one of the following tasks:","pos":[21500,21657]},{"content":"If an Office 365 tenant with that domain name (contoso.edu) exists, Office 365 automatically adds the user to that tenant.","pos":[21661,21783]},{"content":"If an Office 365 tenant with that domain name (contoso.edu) does not exists, Office 365 automatically creates a new Office 365 tenant with that domain name and adds the user to it.","pos":[21786,21966]},{"content":"You will always want faculty and students to join the Office 365 tenant that you created.","pos":[21968,22057]},{"content":"Ensure that you perform the steps in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create a new Office 365 Education subscription<ept id=\"p1\">](#create-a-new-office-365-education-subscription)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Add domains and subdomains<ept id=\"p2\">](#add-domains-and-subdomains)</ept> sections before allowing other faculty and students to join Office 365.","pos":[22058,22330]},{"pos":[22333,22502],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>You cannot merge multiple tenants, so any faculty or students who create their own tenant will need to abandon their existing tenant and join yours."},{"content":"All new Office 365 Education subscriptions have automatic tenant join enabled by default, but you can enable or disable automatic tenant join by using the Windows PowerShell commands in Table 3.","pos":[22504,22698]},{"content":"For more information about how to run these commands, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>How can I prevent students from joining my existing Office 365 tenant<ept id=\"p1\">](https://support.office.com/en-us/article/Office-365-Education-Self-Sign-up-Technical-FAQ-7fb1b2f9-94c2-4cbb-b01e-a6eca34261d6?ui=en-US&amp;rs=en-US&amp;ad=US#BKMK_PreventJoins)</ept>.","pos":[22699,22998]},{"content":"Table 3.","pos":[23001,23009]},{"content":"Windows PowerShell commands to enable or disable Automatic Tenant Join","pos":[23010,23080]},{"content":"Action","pos":[23086,23092]},{"content":"Windows PowerShell command","pos":[23095,23121]},{"content":"Enable","pos":[23166,23172]},{"content":"Disable","pos":[23234,23241]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">\n&gt;**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>If your institution has AD DS, then disable automatic tenant join.","pos":[23305,23394]},{"content":"Instead, use Azure AD integration with AD DS to add users to your Office 365 tenant.","pos":[23395,23479]},{"content":"Disable automatic licensing","pos":[23485,23512]},{"content":"To reduce your administrative effort, automatically assign Office 365 Education or Office 365 Education Plus licenses to faculty and students when they sign up (automatic licensing).","pos":[23514,23696]},{"content":"Automatic licensing also enables Office 365 Education or Office 365 Education Plus features that do not require administrative approval.","pos":[23697,23833]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>By default, automatic licensing is enabled in Office 365 Education.","pos":[23836,23924]},{"content":"If you want to use automatic licensing, then skip this section and go to the next section.","pos":[23925,24015]},{"content":"Although all new Office 365 Education subscriptions have automatic licensing enabled by default, you can enable or disable it for your Office 365 tenant by using the Windows PowerShell commands in Table 4.","pos":[24017,24222]},{"content":"For more information about how to run these commands, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>How can I prevent students from joining my existing Office 365 tenant<ept id=\"p1\">](https://support.office.com/en-us/article/Office-365-Education-Self-Sign-up-Technical-FAQ-7fb1b2f9-94c2-4cbb-b01e-a6eca34261d6?ui=en-US&amp;rs=en-US&amp;ad=US#BKMK_PreventJoins)</ept>.","pos":[24223,24522]},{"content":"Table 4.","pos":[24525,24533]},{"content":"Windows PowerShell commands to enable or disable automatic licensing","pos":[24534,24602]},{"content":"Action","pos":[24607,24613]},{"content":"Windows PowerShell command","pos":[24616,24642]},{"content":"Enable","pos":[24685,24691]},{"content":"Disable","pos":[24752,24759]},{"content":"Enable Azure AD Premium","pos":[24829,24852]},{"content":"When you create your Office 365 subscription, you create an Office 365 tenant that includes an Azure AD directory.","pos":[24854,24968]},{"content":"Azure AD is the centralized repository for all your student and faculty accounts in Office 365, Intune, and other Azure AD–integrated apps.","pos":[24969,25108]},{"content":"Azure AD is available in Free, Basic, and Premium editions.","pos":[25109,25168]},{"content":"Azure AD Free, which is included in Office 365 Education, has fewer features than Azure AD Basic, which in turn has fewer features than Azure AD Premium.","pos":[25169,25322]},{"content":"Educational institutions can obtain Azure AD Basic edition licenses at no cost.","pos":[25324,25403]},{"content":"After you obtain your licenses, activate your Azure AD access by completing the steps in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Step 3: Activate your Azure Active Directory access<ept id=\"p1\">](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/active-directory-get-started-premium/#step-3-activate-your-azure-active-directory-access)</ept>.","pos":[25404,25694]},{"content":"The Azure AD Premium features that are not in Azure AD Basic include:","pos":[25696,25765]},{"content":"Allow designated users to manage group membership","pos":[25769,25818]},{"content":"Dynamic group membership based on user metadata","pos":[25821,25868]},{"content":"Multifactor authentication (MFA)","pos":[25871,25903]},{"content":"Identify cloud apps that your users run","pos":[25906,25945]},{"content":"Automatic enrollment in a mobile device management (MDM) system (such as Intune)","pos":[25948,26028]},{"content":"Self-service recovery of BitLocker","pos":[26031,26065]},{"content":"Add local administrator accounts to Windows 10 devices","pos":[26068,26122]},{"content":"Azure AD Connect health monitoring","pos":[26125,26159]},{"content":"Extended reporting capabilities","pos":[26162,26193]},{"content":"You can assign Azure AD Premium licenses to the users who need these features.","pos":[26195,26273]},{"content":"For example, you may want the users who have access to confidential student information to use MFA.","pos":[26274,26373]},{"content":"In this example, you could assign Azure AD Premium to only those users.","pos":[26374,26445]},{"content":"You can sign up for Azure AD Premium, and then assign licenses to users.","pos":[26447,26519]},{"content":"In this section, you sign up for Azure AD Premium.","pos":[26520,26570]},{"content":"You will assign Azure AD Premium licenses to users later in the deployment process.","pos":[26571,26654]},{"content":"For more information about:","pos":[26656,26683]},{"pos":[26687,26854],"content":"Azure AD editions and the features in each, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure Active Directory editions<ept id=\"p1\">](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/active-directory-editions/)</ept>."},{"pos":[26857,27034],"content":"How to enable Azure AD premium, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Associate an Azure AD directory with a new Azure subscription<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/azure/jj573650.aspx#create_tenant3)</ept>."},{"content":"Summary","pos":[27040,27047]},{"content":"You provision and initially configure Office 365 Education as part of the initial configuration.","pos":[27048,27144]},{"content":"With the subscription in place, automatic tenant join configured, automatic licensing established, and Azure AD Premium enabled (if required), you’re ready to select the method you will use to create user accounts in Office 365.","pos":[27145,27373]},{"content":"Select an Office 365 user account–creation method","pos":[27378,27427]},{"content":"Now that you have an Office 365 subscription, you need to determine how you will create your Office 365 user accounts.","pos":[27430,27548]},{"content":"Use the following methods to create Office 365 user accounts:","pos":[27549,27610]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Method 1:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Automatically synchronize your on-premises AD DS domain with Azure AD.","pos":[27614,27698]},{"content":"Select this method if you have an on-premises AD DS domain.","pos":[27699,27758]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Method 2:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Bulk-import the user accounts from a .csv file (based on information from other sources) into Azure AD.","pos":[27761,27878]},{"content":"Select this method if you don’t have an on-premises AD DS domain.","pos":[27879,27944]},{"content":"Method 1: Automatic synchronization between AD DS and Azure AD","pos":[27950,28012]},{"content":"In this method, you have an on-premises AD DS domain.","pos":[28014,28067]},{"content":"As shown in Figure 4, the Azure AD Connector tool automatically synchronizes AD DS with Azure AD.","pos":[28068,28165]},{"content":"When you add or change any user accounts in AD DS, the Azure AD Connector tool automatically updates Azure AD.","pos":[28166,28276]},{"pos":[28279,28618],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>Azure AD Connect also supports synchronization from any Lightweight Directory Access Protocol version 3 (LDAPv3)–compliant directory by using the information provided in <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Generic LDAP Connector for FIM 2010 R2 Technical Reference<ept id=\"p2\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn510997.aspx?f=255&amp;MSPPError=-2147217396)</ept>."},{"content":"fig 4","pos":[28622,28627]},{"content":"Figure 4.","pos":[28672,28681]},{"content":"Automatic synchronization between AD DS and Azure AD","pos":[28682,28734]},{"pos":[28737,28908],"content":"For more information about how to perform this step, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Integrate on-premises AD DS with Azure AD<ept id=\"p1\">](#integrate-on-premises-ad-ds-with-azure-ad)</ept> section in this guide."},{"content":"Method 2: Bulk import into Azure AD from a .csv file","pos":[28914,28966]},{"content":"In this method, you have no on-premises AD DS domain.","pos":[28968,29021]},{"content":"As shown in Figure 5, you manually prepare a .csv file with the student information from your source, and then manually import the information directly into Azure AD.","pos":[29022,29188]},{"content":"The .csv file must be in the format that Office 365 specifies.","pos":[29189,29251]},{"content":"fig 5","pos":[29255,29260]},{"content":"Figure 5.","pos":[29305,29314]},{"content":"Bulk import into Azure AD from other sources","pos":[29315,29359]},{"content":"To implement this method, perform the following steps:","pos":[29362,29416]},{"content":"Export the student information from the source.","pos":[29421,29468]},{"content":"Ultimately, you want to format the student information in the format the bulk-import feature requires.","pos":[29469,29571]},{"content":"Bulk-import the student information into Azure AD.","pos":[29575,29625]},{"content":"For more information about how to perform this step, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Bulk-import user accounts into Office 365<ept id=\"p1\">](#bulk-import-user-accounts-into-office-365)</ept> section.","pos":[29626,29783]},{"content":"Summary","pos":[29789,29796]},{"content":"In this section, you selected the method for creating user accounts in your Office 365 subscription.","pos":[29798,29898]},{"content":"Ultimately, these user accounts are in Azure AD (which is the identity management system for Office 365).","pos":[29899,30004]},{"content":"Now, you’re ready to create your Office 365 accounts.","pos":[30005,30058]},{"content":"Integrate on-premises AD DS with Azure AD","pos":[30063,30104]},{"content":"You can integrate your on-premises AD DS domain with Azure AD to provide identity management for your Office 365 tenant.","pos":[30106,30226]},{"content":"With this integration, you can synchronize the users, security groups, and distribution lists in your AD DS domain with Azure AD with the Azure AD Connect tool.","pos":[30227,30387]},{"content":"Users will be able to sign in to Office 365 automatically by using their email account and the same password they use to sign in to AD DS.","pos":[30388,30526]},{"pos":[30529,30639],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>If your institution does not have an on-premises AD DS domain, you can skip this section."},{"content":"Select synchronization model","pos":[30645,30673]},{"content":"Before you deploy AD DS and Azure AD synchronization, you need to determine where you want to deploy the server that runs Azure AD Connect.","pos":[30675,30814]},{"content":"You can deploy the Azure AD Connect tool by using one of the following methods:","pos":[30816,30895]},{"content":"On premises.","pos":[30901,30913]},{"content":"As shown in Figure 6, Azure AD Connect runs on premises, which has the advantage of not requiring a virtual private network (VPN) connection to Azure.","pos":[30916,31066]},{"content":"It does, however, require a virtual machine (VM) or physical server.","pos":[31067,31135]},{"content":"fig 6","pos":[31140,31145]},{"content":"Figure 6.","pos":[31191,31200]},{"content":"Azure AD Connect on premises","pos":[31201,31229]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>In Azure<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[31234,31247]},{"content":"As shown in Figure 7, Azure AD Connect runs on a VM in Azure AD, which has the advantages of being faster to provision (than a physical, on-premises server), offers better site availability, and helps reduce the number of on-premises servers.","pos":[31248,31490]},{"content":"The disadvantage is that you need to deploy a VPN gateway on premises.","pos":[31491,31561]},{"content":"fig 7","pos":[31566,31571]},{"content":"Figure 7.","pos":[31617,31626]},{"content":"Azure AD Connect in Azure","pos":[31627,31652]},{"content":"This guide describes how to run Azure AD Connect on premises.","pos":[31655,31716]},{"content":"For information about running Azure AD Connect in Azure, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Deploy Office 365 Directory Synchronization (DirSync) in Microsoft Azure<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn635310.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[31717,31912]},{"content":"Deploy Azure AD Connect on premises","pos":[31918,31953]},{"content":"In this synchronization model (illustrated in Figure 6), you run Azure AD Connect on premises on a physical device or VM.","pos":[31955,32076]},{"content":"Azure AD Connect synchronizes AD DS user and group accounts with Azure AD.","pos":[32077,32151]},{"content":"Azure AD Connect includes a wizard that helps you configure Azure AD Connect for your AD DS domain and Office 365 subscription.","pos":[32152,32279]},{"content":"First, you install Azure AD Connect; then, you run the wizard to configure it for your institution.","pos":[32280,32379]},{"content":"To deploy AD DS and Azure AD synchronization","pos":[32386,32430]},{"pos":[32435,32685],"content":"Configure your environment to meet the prerequisites for installing Azure AD Connect by performing the steps in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Prerequisites for Azure AD Connect<ept id=\"p1\">](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/active-directory-aadconnect-prerequisites/)</ept>."},{"content":"On the VM or physical device that will run Azure AD Connect, sign in with a domain administrator account.","pos":[32689,32794]},{"pos":[32798,32989],"content":"Install Azure AD Connect by performing the steps in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Install Azure AD Connect<ept id=\"p1\">](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/active-directory-aadconnect/#install-azure-ad-connect)</ept>."},{"pos":[32993,33229],"content":"Configure Azure AD Connect features based on your institution’s requirements by performing the steps in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Configure features<ept id=\"p1\">](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/active-directory-aadconnect/#configure-sync-features)</ept>."},{"content":"Now that you have used on premises Azure AD Connect to deploy AD DS and Azure AD synchronization, you’re ready to verify that Azure AD Connect is synchronizing AD DS user and group accounts with Azure AD.","pos":[33231,33435]},{"content":"Verify synchronization","pos":[33441,33463]},{"content":"Azure AD Connect should start synchronization immediately.","pos":[33465,33523]},{"content":"Depending on the number of users in your AD DS domain, the synchronization process can take some time.","pos":[33524,33626]},{"content":"To monitor the process, view the number of AD DS users and groups the tool has synchronized with Azure AD in the Office 365 admin console.","pos":[33627,33765]},{"content":"To verify AD DS and Azure AD synchronization","pos":[33772,33816]},{"content":"Open https://portal.office.com in your web browser.","pos":[33821,33872]},{"pos":[33876,34062],"content":"Using the administrative account that you created in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create a new Office 365 Education subscription<ept id=\"p1\">](#create-a-new-office-365-education-subscription)</ept> section, sign in to Office 365."},{"pos":[34066,34134],"content":"In the list view, expand <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>USERS<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, and then click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Active Users<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>."},{"content":"In the details pane, view the list of users.","pos":[34138,34182]},{"content":"The list of users should mirror the users in AD DS.","pos":[34183,34234]},{"pos":[34238,34273],"content":"In the list view, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>GROUPS<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>."},{"content":"In the details pane, view the list of security groups.","pos":[34277,34331]},{"content":"The list of users should mirror the security groups in AD DS.","pos":[34332,34393]},{"content":"In the details pane, double-click one of the security groups.","pos":[34397,34458]},{"content":"The list of security group members should mirror the group membership for the corresponding security group in AD DS.","pos":[34462,34578]},{"content":"Close the browser.","pos":[34582,34600]},{"content":"Now that you have verified Azure AD Connect synchronization, you’re ready to assign user licenses for Azure AD Premium.","pos":[34602,34721]},{"content":"Summary","pos":[34727,34734]},{"content":"In this section, you selected your synchronization model, deployed Azure AD Connect, and verified that Azure AD is synchronizing properly.","pos":[34736,34874]},{"content":"Bulk-import user and group accounts into AD DS","pos":[34879,34925]},{"content":"You can bulk-import user and group accounts into your on-premises AD DS domain.","pos":[34927,35006]},{"content":"Bulk-importing accounts helps reduce the time and effort needed to create users compared to creating the accounts manually in the Office 365 Admin portal.","pos":[35007,35161]},{"content":"First, you select the appropriate method for bulk-importing user accounts into AD DS.","pos":[35162,35247]},{"content":"Next, you create the .csv file that contains the user accounts.","pos":[35248,35311]},{"content":"Finally, you use the selected method to import the .csv file into AD DS.","pos":[35312,35384]},{"pos":[35387,35496],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>If your institution doesn’t have an on-premises AD DS domain, you can skip this section."},{"content":"Select the bulk import method","pos":[35502,35531]},{"content":"Several methods are available to bulk-import user accounts into AD DS domains.","pos":[35533,35611]},{"content":"Table 5 lists the methods that the Windows Server operating system supports natively.","pos":[35612,35697]},{"content":"In addition, you can use partner solutions to bulk-import user and group accounts into AD DS.","pos":[35698,35791]},{"content":"Table 5.","pos":[35794,35802]},{"content":"AD DS bulk-import account methods","pos":[35803,35836]},{"content":"Method","pos":[35840,35846]},{"content":"Description and reason to select this method","pos":[35849,35893]},{"content":"Ldifde.exe","pos":[35954,35964]},{"content":"This command-line tool allows you to import and export objects (such as user accounts) from AD DS.","pos":[35966,36064]},{"content":"Select this method if you aren’t comfortable with Microsoft Visual Basic Scripting Edition (VBScript), Windows PowerShell, or other scripting languages.","pos":[36065,36217]},{"content":"For more information about using Ldifde.exe, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Step-by-Step Guide to Bulk Import and Export to Active Directory<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb727091.aspx)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>LDIFDE—Export/Import data from Active Directory—LDIFDE commands<ept id=\"p2\">](https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/kb/555636)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>Import or Export Directory Objects Using Ldifde<ept id=\"p3\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/cc816781.aspx)</ept>, and <bpt id=\"p4\">[</bpt>LDIFDE<ept id=\"p4\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/cc755456.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[36218,36678]},{"content":"VBScript","pos":[36681,36689]},{"content":"This scripting language uses the Active Directory Services Interfaces (ADSI) Component Object Model interface to manage AD DS objects, including user and group objects.","pos":[36692,36860]},{"content":"Select this method if you’re comfortable with VBScript.","pos":[36861,36916]},{"content":"For more information about using VBScript and ADSI, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Step-by-Step Guide to Bulk Import and Export to Active Directory<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb727091.aspx)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>ADSI Scriptomatic<ept id=\"p2\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/scriptcenter/dd939958.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[36917,37187]},{"content":"Windows PowerShell","pos":[37190,37208]},{"content":"This scripting language natively supports cmdlets to manage AD DS objects, including user and group objects.","pos":[37210,37318]},{"content":"Select this method if you’re comfortable with Window PowerShell scripting.","pos":[37319,37393]},{"content":"For more information about using Windows PowerShell, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Import Bulk Users to Active Directory<ept id=\"p1\">](https://blogs.technet.microsoft.com/bettertogether/2011/01/09/import-bulk-users-to-active-directory/)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>PowerShell: Bulk create AD Users from CSV file<ept id=\"p2\">](http://social.technet.microsoft.com/wiki/contents/articles/24541.powershell-bulk-create-ad-users-from-csv-file.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[37394,37763]},{"content":"Create a source file that contains the user and group accounts","pos":[37773,37835]},{"content":"After you have selected your user and group account bulk import method, you’re ready to create the source file that contains the user and group account.","pos":[37837,37989]},{"content":"You’ll use the source file as the input to the import process.","pos":[37990,38052]},{"content":"The source file format depends on the method you selected.","pos":[38053,38111]},{"content":"Table 6 lists the source file format for the bulk import methods.","pos":[38112,38177]},{"content":"Table 6.","pos":[38180,38188]},{"content":"Source file format for each bulk import method","pos":[38189,38235]},{"content":"Method","pos":[38240,38246]},{"content":"Source file format","pos":[38249,38267]},{"content":"Ldifde.exe","pos":[38303,38313]},{"content":"Ldifde.exe requires a specific format for the source file.","pos":[38314,38372]},{"content":"Use Ldifde.exe to export existing user and group accounts so that you can see the format.","pos":[38373,38462]},{"content":"For examples of the format that Ldifde.exe requires, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Step-by-Step Guide to Bulk Import and Export to Active Directory<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb727091.aspx)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>LDIFDE—Export/Import data from Active Directory—LDIFDE commands<ept id=\"p2\">](https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/kb/555636)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>Import or Export Directory Objects Using Ldifde<ept id=\"p3\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/cc816781.aspx)</ept>, and <bpt id=\"p4\">[</bpt>LDIFDE<ept id=\"p4\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/cc755456.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[38463,38931]},{"content":"VBScript","pos":[38934,38942]},{"content":"VBScript can use any .csv file format to create a source file for the bulk-import process.","pos":[38945,39035]},{"content":"To create the .csv file, use software such as Excel.","pos":[39036,39088]},{"content":"For examples of how to format your source file in comma-separated values (CSV) format, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Step-by-Step Guide to Bulk Import and Export to Active Directory<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb727091.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[39089,39306]},{"content":"Windows PowerShell","pos":[39310,39328]},{"content":"Windows PowerShell can use any .csv file format you want to create as a source file for the bulk-import process.","pos":[39330,39442]},{"content":"To create the .csv file, use software such as Excel.","pos":[39443,39495]},{"content":"For examples of how to format your source file in CSV format, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Import Bulk Users to Active Directory<ept id=\"p1\">](https://blogs.technet.microsoft.com/bettertogether/2011/01/09/import-bulk-users-to-active-directory/)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>PowerShell: Bulk create AD Users from CSV file<ept id=\"p2\">](http://social.technet.microsoft.com/wiki/contents/articles/24541.powershell-bulk-create-ad-users-from-csv-file.aspx)</ept>.","pos":[39496,39874]},{"content":"Import the user accounts into AD DS","pos":[39884,39919]},{"content":"With the bulk-import source file finished, you’re ready to import the user and group accounts into AD DS.","pos":[39921,40026]},{"content":"The steps for importing the file are slightly different for each method.","pos":[40027,40099]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>Bulk-import your group accounts first, and then import your user accounts.","pos":[40102,40197]},{"content":"Importing in this order allows you to specify group membership when you import your user accounts.","pos":[40198,40296]},{"content":"For more information about how to import user accounts into AD DS by using:","pos":[40299,40374]},{"pos":[40378,40805],"content":"Ldifde.exe, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Step-by-Step Guide to Bulk Import and Export to Active Directory<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb727091.aspx)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>LDIFDE—Export/Import data from Active Directory—LDIFDE commands<ept id=\"p2\">](https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/kb/555636)</ept>, <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>Import or Export Directory Objects Using Ldifde<ept id=\"p3\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/cc816781.aspx)</ept>, and <bpt id=\"p4\">[</bpt>LDIFDE<ept id=\"p4\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/cc755456.aspx)</ept>."},{"pos":[40808,40948],"content":"VBScript, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Step-by-Step Guide to Bulk Import and Export to Active Directory<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb727091.aspx)</ept>."},{"pos":[40951,41287],"content":"Windows PowerShell, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Import Bulk Users to Active Directory<ept id=\"p1\">](https://blogs.technet.microsoft.com/bettertogether/2011/01/09/import-bulk-users-to-active-directory/)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>PowerShell: Bulk create AD Users from CSV file<ept id=\"p2\">](http://social.technet.microsoft.com/wiki/contents/articles/24541.powershell-bulk-create-ad-users-from-csv-file.aspx)</ept>."},{"content":"Summary","pos":[41293,41300]},{"content":"In this section, you selected the bulk-import method, created the source file that contains the user and group accounts, and imported the user and group accounts in to AD DS.","pos":[41302,41476]},{"content":"If you have Azure AD Connect, it automatically synchronizes the new AD DS user and group accounts to Azure AD.","pos":[41477,41587]},{"content":"Now, you’re ready to assign user licenses for Azure AD Premium in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Assign user licenses for Azure AD Premium<ept id=\"p1\">](#assign-user-licenses-for-azure-ad-premium)</ept> section later in this guide.","pos":[41588,41774]},{"content":"Bulk-import user accounts into Office 365","pos":[41779,41820]},{"content":"You can bulk-import user and group accounts directly into Office 365, reducing the time and effort required to create users.","pos":[41822,41946]},{"content":"First, you bulk-import the user accounts into Office 365.","pos":[41947,42004]},{"content":"Then, you create the security groups for your institution.","pos":[42005,42063]},{"content":"Finally, you create the email distribution groups your institution requires.","pos":[42064,42140]},{"content":"Create user accounts in Office 365","pos":[42146,42180]},{"content":"Now that you have created your new Office 365 Education subscription, you need to create user accounts.","pos":[42182,42285]},{"content":"You can add user accounts for the teachers, other faculty, and students who will use the classroom.","pos":[42286,42385]},{"content":"You can use the Office 365 admin center to add individual Office 365 accounts manually—a reasonable process when you’re adding only a few users.","pos":[42387,42531]},{"content":"If you have many users, however, you can automate the process by creating a list of those users, and then use that list to create user accounts (that is, bulk-add users).","pos":[42532,42702]},{"content":"The bulk-add process assigns the same Office 365 Education license plan to all users on the list.","pos":[42704,42801]},{"content":"Therefore, you must create a separate list for each license plan you recorded in Table 2.","pos":[42802,42891]},{"content":"Depending on the number of faculty members who need to use the classroom, you may want to add the faculty Office 365 accounts manually; however, use the bulk-add process to add student accounts.","pos":[42892,43086]},{"pos":[43088,43370],"content":"For more information about how to bulk-add users to Office 365, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Add several users at the same time to Office 365<ept id=\"p1\">](https://support.office.com/en-us/article/Add-several-users-at-the-same-time-to-Office-365-Admin-Help-1f5767ed-e717-4f24-969c-6ea9d412ca88?ui=en-US&amp;rs=en-US&amp;ad=US)</ept>."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>If you encountered errors during bulk add, resolve them before you continue the bulk-add process.","pos":[43373,43491]},{"content":"You can view the log file to see which users caused the errors, and then modify the .csv file to correct the problems.","pos":[43492,43610]},{"content":"Click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Back<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to retry the verification process.","pos":[43611,43660]},{"content":"The email accounts are assigned temporary passwords upon creation.","pos":[43662,43728]},{"content":"You must communicate these temporary passwords to your users before they can sign in to Office 365.","pos":[43729,43828]},{"content":"Create Office 365 security groups","pos":[43834,43867]},{"content":"Assign SharePoint Online resource permissions to Office 365 security groups, not individual user accounts.","pos":[43869,43975]},{"content":"For example, create one security group for faculty members and another for students.","pos":[43976,44060]},{"content":"Then, you can assign unique SharePoint Online resource permissions to faculty members and a different set of permissions to students.","pos":[44061,44194]},{"content":"Add or remove users from the security groups to grant or revoke access to SharePoint Online resources.","pos":[44195,44297]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>If your institution has AD DS, don’t create security accounts in Office 365.","pos":[44300,44397]},{"content":"Instead, create the security groups in AD DS, and then use Azure AD integration to synchronize the security groups with your Office 365 tenant.","pos":[44398,44541]},{"pos":[44543,44820],"content":"For information about creating security groups, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create and manage Office 365 groups in Admin Center Preview<ept id=\"p1\">](https://support.office.com/en-us/article/Create-and-manage-Office-365-groups-in-Admin-Center-Preview-93df5bd4-74c4-45e8-9625-56db92865a6e?ui=en-US&amp;rs=en-US&amp;ad=US)</ept>."},{"content":"You can add and remove users from security groups at any time.","pos":[44822,44884]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>Office 365 evaluates group membership when users sign in.","pos":[44887,44965]},{"content":"If you change group membership for a user, that user may need to sign out, and then sign in again for the change to take effect.","pos":[44966,45094]},{"content":"Create email distribution groups","pos":[45100,45132]},{"content":"Microsoft Exchange Online uses an email distribution group as a single email recipient for multiple users.","pos":[45134,45240]},{"content":"For example, you could create an email distribution group that contains all students.","pos":[45241,45326]},{"content":"Then, you could send a message to the email distribution group instead of individually addressing the message to each student.","pos":[45327,45453]},{"content":"You can create email distribution groups based on job role (such as teachers, administration, or students) or specific interests (such as robotics, drama club, or soccer team).","pos":[45455,45631]},{"content":"You can create any number of distribution groups, and users can be members of more than one group.","pos":[45632,45730]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>Office 365 can take some time to complete the Exchange Online creation process.","pos":[45733,45833]},{"content":"You will have to wait until Office 365 completes the Exchange Online creation process before you can perform the following steps.","pos":[45834,45963]},{"pos":[45966,46248],"content":"For information about how to create security groups, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create and manage Office 365 groups in Admin Center Preview<ept id=\"p1\">](https://support.office.com/en-us/article/Create-and-manage-Office-365-groups-in-Admin-Center-Preview-93df5bd4-74c4-45e8-9625-56db92865a6e?ui=en-US&amp;rs=en-US&amp;ad=US)</ept>."},{"content":"Summary","pos":[46254,46261]},{"content":"Now, you have bulk-imported the user accounts into Office 365.","pos":[46263,46325]},{"content":"First, you selected the bulk-import method.","pos":[46326,46369]},{"content":"Next, you created the Office 365 security groups in Office 365.","pos":[46370,46433]},{"content":"Finally, you created the Office 365 email distribution groups.","pos":[46434,46496]},{"content":"Now, you’re ready to assign user licenses for Azure AD Premium.","pos":[46497,46560]},{"content":"Assign user licenses for Azure AD Premium","pos":[46565,46606]},{"content":"Azure AD is available in Free, Basic, and Premium editions.","pos":[46608,46667]},{"content":"Azure AD Free, which is included in Office 365 Education, has fewer features than Azure AD Basic, which in turn has fewer features than Azure AD Premium.","pos":[46668,46821]},{"content":"Educational institutions can obtain Azure AD Basic licenses at no cost and Azure AD Premium licenses at a reduced cost.","pos":[46822,46941]},{"content":"You can assign Azure AD Premium licenses to the users who need the features this edition offers.","pos":[46943,47039]},{"content":"For example, you may want the users who have access to confidential student information to use MFA.","pos":[47040,47139]},{"content":"In this example, you could assign Azure AD Premium only to those users.","pos":[47140,47211]},{"content":"For more information about:","pos":[47213,47240]},{"pos":[47244,47386],"content":"Azure AD editions, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure Active Directory editions<ept id=\"p1\">](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/active-directory-editions/)</ept>."},{"pos":[47389,47633],"content":"How to assign user licenses for Azure AD Premium, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>How to assign EMS/Azure AD Premium licenses to user accounts<ept id=\"p1\">](https://channel9.msdn.com/Series/Azure-Active-Directory-Videos-Demos/How-to-assign-Azure-AD-Premium-Licenses-to-user-accounts)</ept>."},{"content":"Create and configure a Windows Store for Business portal","pos":[47638,47694]},{"content":"Windows Store for Business allows you to create your own private portal to manage Windows Store apps in your institution.","pos":[47696,47817]},{"content":"With Windows Store for Business, you can do the following:","pos":[47818,47876]},{"content":"Find and acquire Windows Store apps.","pos":[47880,47916]},{"content":"Manage apps, app licenses, and updates.","pos":[47919,47958]},{"content":"Distribute apps to your users.","pos":[47961,47991]},{"pos":[47994,48182],"content":"For more information about Windows Store for Business, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Store for Business overview<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/whats-new/windows-store-for-business-overview)</ept>."},{"content":"The following section shows you how to create a Windows Store for Business portal and configure it for your school.","pos":[48184,48299]},{"content":"Create and configure your Windows Store for Business portal","pos":[48305,48364]},{"content":"To create and configure your Windows Store for Business portal, simply use the administrative account for your Office 365 subscription to sign in to Windows Store for Business.","pos":[48366,48542]},{"content":"Windows Store for Business automatically creates a portal for your institution and uses your account as its administrator.","pos":[48543,48665]},{"content":"To create and configure a Windows Store for Business portal","pos":[48672,48731]},{"pos":[48736,48838],"content":"In Microsoft Edge or Internet Explorer, type <ph id=\"ph1\">`http://microsoft.com/business-store`</ph> in the address bar."},{"pos":[48842,48935],"content":"On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows Store for Business<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Sign in with an organizational account<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>If your institution has AD DS, then don’t create security accounts in Office 365.","pos":[48937,49039]},{"content":"Instead, create the security groups in AD DS, and then use Azure AD integration to synchronize the security groups with your Office 365 tenant.","pos":[49040,49183]},{"pos":[49187,49434],"content":"On the Windows Store for Business sign-in page, use the administrative account for the Office 365 subscription you created in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create a new Office 365 Education subscription<ept id=\"p1\">](#create-a-new-office-365-education-subscription)</ept> section to sign in."},{"pos":[49438,49673],"content":"On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows Store for Business Services Agreement<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, review the agreement, select the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>I accept this agreement and certify that I have the authority to bind my organization to its terms<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> check box, and then click <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Accept<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>"},{"pos":[49677,49755],"content":"In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Welcome to the Windows Store for Business<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> dialog box, click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>OK<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>."},{"content":"After you create the Windows Store for Business portal, configure it by using the commands in the settings menu listed in Table 7.","pos":[49757,49887]},{"content":"Depending on your institution, you may (or may not) need to change these settings to further customize your portal.","pos":[49888,50003]},{"content":"Table 7.","pos":[50007,50015]},{"content":"Menu selections to configure Windows Store for Business settings","pos":[50016,50080]},{"content":"Menu selection","pos":[50085,50099]},{"content":"What you can do in this menu","pos":[50109,50137]},{"content":"Account information","pos":[50180,50199]},{"content":"Displays information about your Windows Store for Business account (no settings can be changed).","pos":[50200,50296]},{"content":"You make changes to this information in Office 365 or the Azure Portal.","pos":[50297,50368]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Update Windows Store for Business account settings<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/manage/update-windows-store-for-business-account-settings)</ept>.","pos":[50369,50551]},{"content":"Device Guard signing","pos":[50554,50574]},{"content":"Allows you to upload and sign Device Guard catalog and policy files.","pos":[50575,50643]},{"content":"For more information about Device Guard, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Device Guard deployment guide<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/keep-secure/device-guard-deployment-guide)</ept>.","pos":[50644,50808]},{"content":"LOB publishers","pos":[50811,50825]},{"content":"Allows you to add line-of-business (LOB) publishers that can then publish apps to your private store.","pos":[50827,50928]},{"content":"LOB publishers are usually internal developers or software vendors that are working with your institution.","pos":[50929,51035]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Working with line-of-business apps<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/manage/working-with-line-of-business-apps)</ept>.","pos":[51036,51186]},{"content":"Management tools","pos":[51189,51205]},{"content":"Allows you to add tools that you can use to distribute (deploy) apps in your private store.","pos":[51207,51298]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Distribute apps with a management tool<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/manage/distribute-apps-with-management-tool)</ept>.","pos":[51299,51455]},{"content":"Offline licensing","pos":[51458,51475]},{"content":"Allows you to show (or not show) offline licensed apps to people shopping in your private store.","pos":[51476,51572]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Licensing model: online and offline licenses<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/manage/apps-in-windows-store-for-business#licensing-model)</ept>.","pos":[51573,51749]},{"content":"Permissions","pos":[51752,51763]},{"content":"Allows you to grant other users in your organization the ability to buy, manage, and administer your Windows Store for Business portal.","pos":[51764,51899]},{"content":"You can also remove permissions you have previously granted.","pos":[51900,51960]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Roles and permissions in Windows Store for Business<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/manage/roles-and-permissions-windows-store-for-business)</ept>.","pos":[51961,52142]},{"content":"Private store","pos":[52145,52158]},{"content":"Allows you to change the organization name used in your Windows Store for Business portal.","pos":[52159,52249]},{"content":"When you create your portal, the private store uses the organization name that you used to create your Office 365 subscription.","pos":[52250,52377]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Distribute apps using your private store<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/manage/distribute-apps-from-your-private-store)</ept>.","pos":[52378,52539]},{"content":"Find, acquire, and distribute apps in the portal","pos":[52549,52597]},{"content":"Now that you have created your Windows Store for Business portal, you’re ready to find, acquire, and distribute apps that you will add to your portal.","pos":[52599,52749]},{"content":"You do this by using the Inventory page in Windows Store for Business.","pos":[52750,52820]},{"pos":[52823,52963],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>Your educational institution can now use a credit card or purchase order to pay for apps in Windows Store for Business."},{"content":"You can deploy apps to individual users or make apps available to users through your private store.","pos":[52965,53064]},{"content":"Deploying apps to individual users restricts the app to those specified users.","pos":[53065,53143]},{"content":"Making apps available through your private store allows all your users.","pos":[53144,53215]},{"pos":[53217,53469],"content":"For more information about how to find, acquire, and distribute apps in the portal, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>App inventory management for Windows Store for Business<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/manage/app-inventory-managemement-windows-store-for-business)</ept>."},{"content":"Summary","pos":[53475,53482]},{"content":"At the end of this section, you should have a properly configured Windows Store for Business portal.","pos":[53484,53584]},{"content":"You have also found and acquired your apps from Windows Store.","pos":[53585,53647]},{"content":"Finally, you should have deployed all your Windows Store apps to your users.","pos":[53648,53724]},{"content":"Now, you’re ready to deploy Windows Store apps to your users.","pos":[53725,53786]},{"content":"Plan for deployment","pos":[53791,53810]},{"content":"You will use the LTI deployment process in MDT to deploy Windows 10 to devices or to upgrade devices to Windows 10.","pos":[53812,53927]},{"content":"Prior to preparing for deployment, you must make some deployment planning decisions, including selecting the operating systems you will use, the approach you will use to create your Windows 10 images, and the method you will use to initiate the LTI deployment process.","pos":[53928,54196]},{"content":"Select the operating systems","pos":[54202,54230]},{"content":"Later in the process, you will import the versions of Windows 10 you want to deploy.","pos":[54232,54316]},{"content":"You can deploy the operating system to new devices, refresh existing devices, or upgrade existing devices.","pos":[54317,54423]},{"content":"In the case of:","pos":[54424,54439]},{"content":"New devices or refreshing existing devices, you will complete replace the existing operating system on a device with Windows 10.","pos":[54443,54571]},{"content":"Upgrading existing devices, you will upgrade the existing operating system (the Windows 8.1 or Windows 7 operating system) to Windows 10.","pos":[54574,54711]},{"content":"Depending on your school’s requirements, you may need any combination of the following Windows 10 editions:","pos":[54713,54820]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows 10 Home<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[54824,54844]},{"content":"Use this operating system to upgrade existing eligible institution-owned and personal devices that are running Windows 8.1 Home or Windows 7 Home to Windows 10 Home.","pos":[54845,55010]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows 10 Pro<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[55013,55032]},{"content":"Use this operating system to:","pos":[55033,55062]},{"content":"Upgrade existing eligible institution-owned and personal devices running Windows 8.1 Pro or Windows 7 Professional to Windows 10 Pro.","pos":[55066,55199]},{"content":"Deploy new instances of Windows 10 Pro to devices so that new devices have a known configuration.","pos":[55203,55300]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Windows 10 Education<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[55303,55328]},{"content":"Use this operating system to:","pos":[55329,55358]},{"content":"Upgrade institution-owned devices to Windows 10 Education.","pos":[55362,55420]},{"content":"Deploy new instances of Windows 10 Education so that new devices have a known configuration.","pos":[55424,55516]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>Although you can use Windows 10 Home on institution-owned devices, Microsoft recommends that you use Windows 10 Pro or Windows 10 Education, instead.","pos":[55519,55689]},{"content":"Windows 10 Pro and Windows 10 Education provide support for MDM, policy-based management, and Windows Store for Business.","pos":[55690,55811]},{"content":"These features are not available in Windows 10 Home.","pos":[55812,55864]},{"content":"One other consideration is the mix of processor architectures you will support.","pos":[55866,55945]},{"content":"If you can, support only 64-bit versions of Windows 10.","pos":[55946,56001]},{"content":"If you have devices that can run only 32 bit versions of Windows 10, you will need to import both 64-bit and 32-bit versions of the Windows 10 editions listed above.","pos":[56002,56167]},{"pos":[56170,56418],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>On devices that have minimal system resources (such as devices with only 2 GB of memory or 32 GB of storage), use 32-bit versions of Windows 10 because 64-bit versions of Windows 10 place more stress on device system resources."},{"content":"Finally, as a best practice, minimize the number of operating systems that you deploy and manage.","pos":[56420,56517]},{"content":"If possible, standardize institution-owned devices on one Windows 10 edition (such as a 64-bit version of Windows 10 Education or Windows 10 Pro).","pos":[56518,56664]},{"content":"Of course, you cannot standardize personal devices on a specific operating system version or processor architecture.","pos":[56665,56781]},{"content":"Select an image approach","pos":[56787,56811]},{"content":"A key operating system image decision is whether to use a “thin” or “thick” image.","pos":[56813,56895]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Thin images<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> contain only the operating system, and MDT installs the necessary device drivers and apps after the operating system has been installed.","pos":[56896,57046]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Thick images<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> contain the operating system, “core” apps (such as Office), and device drivers.","pos":[57047,57141]},{"content":"With thick images, MDT installs any device drivers and apps not included in the thick image after the operating system has been installed.","pos":[57142,57280]},{"content":"The advantage to a thin image is that the final deployment configuration is dynamic, and you can easily change the configuration without having to capture another image.","pos":[57282,57451]},{"content":"The disadvantage of a thin image is that it takes longer to complete the deployment.","pos":[57452,57536]},{"content":"The advantage of a thick image is that the deployment takes less time than it would for a thin image.","pos":[57538,57639]},{"content":"The disadvantage of a thick image is that you need to capture a new image each time you want to make a change to the operating system, apps, or other software in the image.","pos":[57640,57812]},{"content":"Select a method to initiate deployment","pos":[57818,57856]},{"content":"The MDT deployment process is highly automated, requiring minimal information to deploy or upgrade Windows 10, but you must manually initiate the MDT deployment process.","pos":[57858,58027]},{"content":"To do so, use the method listed in Table 8 that best meets the needs of your institution.","pos":[58028,58117]},{"content":"Table 8.","pos":[58120,58128]},{"content":"Methods to initiate MDT deployment","pos":[58129,58163]},{"content":"Method","pos":[58279,58285]},{"content":"Description and reason to select this method","pos":[58308,58352]},{"content":"Windows Deployment Services","pos":[58404,58431]},{"content":"This method:","pos":[58441,58453]},{"content":"Uses diskless booting to initiate MDT deployment.","pos":[58473,58522]},{"content":"Works only with devices that support PXE boot.","pos":[58532,58578]},{"content":"Deploys Windows 10 over the network, which consumes more network bandwidth than deployment from local media.","pos":[58588,58696]},{"content":"Deploys images more slowly than when using local media.","pos":[58706,58761]},{"content":"Requires that you deploy a Windows Deployment Services server.","pos":[58771,58833]},{"content":"Select this method when you want to deploy Windows over-the-network and perform diskless booting.","pos":[58846,58943]},{"content":"The advantage of this method is that the diskless media are generic and typically don’t require updates after you create them (the Deployment Wizard accesses the centrally located deployment share over the network).","pos":[58944,59159]},{"content":"The disadvantage of this method is that over-the-network deployments are slower than deployments from local media, and you must deploy a Windows Deployment Services server.","pos":[59160,59332]},{"content":"Bootable media","pos":[59367,59381]},{"content":"This method:","pos":[59391,59403]},{"content":"Initiates MDT deployment by booting from local media, including from USB drives, DVD-ROM, or CD-ROM.","pos":[59423,59523]},{"content":"Deploys Windows 10 over the network, which consumes more network bandwidth than deployment from local media.","pos":[59533,59641]},{"content":"Deploys images more slowly than when using local media.","pos":[59651,59706]},{"content":"Requires no additional infrastructure.","pos":[59716,59754]},{"content":"Select this method when you want to deploy Windows over-the-network and are willing to boot the target device from local media.","pos":[59768,59895]},{"content":"The advantage of this method is that the media are generic and typically don’t require updates after you create them (the Deployment Wizard accesses the centrally located deployment share over the network).","pos":[59896,60102]},{"content":"The disadvantage of this method is that over-the-network deployments are slower than deployment from local media.","pos":[60103,60216]},{"content":"MDT deployment media","pos":[60251,60271]},{"content":"This method:","pos":[60281,60293]},{"content":"Initiates MDT deployment by booting from a local USB hard disk.","pos":[60313,60376]},{"content":"Deploys Windows 10 from local media, which consumes less network bandwidth than over-the-network methods.","pos":[60386,60491]},{"content":"Deploys images more quickly than network-based methods do.","pos":[60501,60559]},{"content":"Requires a USB hard disk because of the deployment share’s storage requirements (up to 100 GB).","pos":[60569,60664]},{"content":"Select this method when you want to perform local deployments and are willing to boot the target device from a local USB hard disk.","pos":[60677,60808]},{"content":"The advantage of this method is that local deployments are faster than over-the-network deployments.","pos":[60809,60909]},{"content":"The disadvantage of this method is that each time you change the deployment share, you must regenerate the MDT deployment media and update the USB hard disk.","pos":[60910,61067]},{"content":"Summary","pos":[61102,61109]},{"content":"At the end of this section, you should know the Windows 10 editions and processor architecture that you want to deploy (and will import later in the process).","pos":[61111,61269]},{"content":"You also determined whether you want to use thin or thick images.","pos":[61270,61335]},{"content":"Finally, you selected the method for initiating your LTI deployment.","pos":[61336,61404]},{"content":"Now, you can prepare for Windows 10 deployment.","pos":[61405,61452]},{"content":"Prepare for deployment","pos":[61457,61479]},{"content":"To deploy Windows 10 to devices, using the LTI deployment method in MDT.","pos":[61481,61553]},{"content":"In this section, you prepare your MDT environment and Windows Deployment Services for Windows 10 deployment.","pos":[61554,61662]},{"content":"Configure the MDT deployment share","pos":[61668,61702]},{"content":"The first step in preparation for Windows 10 deployment is to configure—that is, <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>populate<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>—the MDT deployment share.","pos":[61704,61821]},{"content":"Table 9 lists the MDT deployment share configuration tasks that you must perform.","pos":[61822,61903]},{"content":"Perform the tasks in the order represented in Table 9.","pos":[61904,61958]},{"content":"Table 9.","pos":[61961,61969]},{"content":"Tasks to configure the MDT deployment share","pos":[61970,62013]},{"content":"Task","pos":[62126,62130]},{"content":"Description","pos":[62153,62164]},{"content":"Import operating systems","pos":[62218,62242]},{"content":"Import the operating systems that you selected in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Select operating systems<ept id=\"p1\">](#select-the-operating-systems)</ept> section into the deployment share.","pos":[62252,62398]},{"content":"For more information about how to import operating systems, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Import an Operating System into the Deployment Workbench<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn759415.aspx#ImportanOperatingSystemintotheDeploymentWorkbench)</ept>.","pos":[62399,62631]},{"content":"Import device drives","pos":[62669,62689]},{"content":"Device drivers allow Windows 10 to know a device’s hardware resources and connected hardware accessories.","pos":[62699,62804]},{"content":"Without the proper device drivers, certain features may be unavailable.","pos":[62805,62876]},{"content":"For example, without the proper audio driver, a device cannot play sounds; without the proper camera driver, the device cannot take photos or use video chat.","pos":[62877,63034]},{"content":"Import device drivers for each device in your institution.","pos":[63046,63104]},{"content":"For more information about how to import device drivers, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Import Device Drivers into the Deployment Workbench<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn759415.aspx#ImportDeviceDriversintotheDeploymentWorkbench)</ept>.","pos":[63105,63325]},{"content":"Create MDT applications for Windows Store apps","pos":[63365,63411]},{"content":"Create an MDT application for each Windows Store app you want to deploy.","pos":[63421,63493]},{"content":"You can deploy Windows Store apps by using <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>sideloading<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>, which allows you to use the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Add-AppxPackage<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> Windows PowerShell cmdlet to deploy the .appx files associated with the app (called <bpt id=\"p3\">*</bpt>provisioned apps<ept id=\"p3\">*</ept>).","pos":[63494,63704]},{"content":"Use this method to deploy up to 24 apps to Windows 10.","pos":[63705,63759]},{"content":"Prior to sideloading the .appx files, obtain the Windows Store .appx files that you will use to deploy (sideload) the apps in your provisioning package.","pos":[63771,63923]},{"content":"For apps in Windows Store, you will need to obtain the .appx files from the app software vendor directly.","pos":[63924,64029]},{"content":"If you are unable to obtain the .appx files from the app software vendor, then you or the students will need to install the apps on the student devices directly from Windows Store or Windows Store for Business.","pos":[64030,64240]},{"content":"If you have Intune, you can deploy Windows Store apps after you deploy Windows 10, as described in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Deploy apps by using Intune<ept id=\"p1\">](#deploy-apps-by-using-intune)</ept> section.","pos":[64252,64423]},{"content":"This method provides granular deployment of Windows Store apps, and you can use it for ongoing management of Windows Store apps.","pos":[64424,64552]},{"content":"This is the preferred method of deploying and managing Windows Store apps.","pos":[64553,64627]},{"content":"In addition, you must prepare your environment for sideloading (deploying) Windows Store apps.","pos":[64639,64733]},{"content":"For more information about how to:","pos":[64734,64768]},{"content":"Prepare your environment for sideloading, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Sideload LOB apps in Windows 10<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/itpro/windows/deploy/sideload-apps-in-windows-10)</ept>.","pos":[64788,64954]},{"content":"Create an MDT application, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create a New Application in the Deployment Workbench<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn759415.aspx#CreateaNewApplicationintheDeploymentWorkbench)</ept>.","pos":[64964,65155]},{"content":"Create MDT applications for Windows desktop apps","pos":[65207,65255]},{"content":"You need to create an MDT application for each Windows desktop app you want to deploy.","pos":[65266,65352]},{"content":"You can obtain the Windows desktop apps from any source, but ensure that you have sufficient licenses for them.","pos":[65353,65464]},{"content":"To help reduce the effort needed to deploy Microsoft Office 2016 desktop apps, use the Office Deployment Tool, as described in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Deploy Click-to-Run for Office 365 products by using the Office Deployment Tool<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/jj219423.aspx?f=255&amp;MSPPError=-2147217396)</ept>.","pos":[65476,65772]},{"content":"If you have Intune, you can deploy Windows desktop apps after you deploy Windows 10, as described in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Deploy apps by using Intune<ept id=\"p1\">](#deploy-apps-by-using-intune)</ept> section.","pos":[65784,65957]},{"content":"This method provides granular deployment of Windows desktop apps, and you can use it for ongoing management of the apps.","pos":[65958,66078]},{"content":"This is the preferred method for deploying and managing Windows desktop apps.","pos":[66079,66156]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>You can also deploy Windows desktop apps after you deploy Windows 10, as described in the <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Deploy apps by using Intune<ept id=\"p2\">](#deploy-apps-by-using-intune)</ept> section.","pos":[66166,66345]},{"pos":[66357,66606],"content":"For more information about how to create an MDT application for Window desktop apps, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create a New Application in the Deployment Workbench<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn759415.aspx#CreateaNewApplicationintheDeploymentWorkbench)</ept>."},{"content":"Create task sequences.","pos":[66647,66669]},{"content":"You must create a separate task sequences for each Windows 10 edition, processor architecture, operating system upgrade process, and new operating system deployment process.","pos":[66680,66853]},{"content":"Minimally, create a task sequence for each Windows 10 operating system you imported in Step 1—for example, (1) if you want to deploy Windows 10 Education to new devices or refresh existing devices with a new deployment of Windows 10 Education; (2) if you want to upgrade existing devices running Windows 8.1 or Windows 7 to Windows 10 Education; or (3) if you want to run deployments and upgrades for both 32 bit and 64 bit versions of Windows 10.","pos":[66854,67301]},{"content":"To do so, you must create task sequences that will:","pos":[67302,67353]},{"content":"Deploy Windows 10 Education 64-bit to devices.","pos":[67373,67419]},{"content":"Deploy Windows 10 Education 32-bit to devices.","pos":[67429,67475]},{"content":"Upgrade existing devices to Windows 10 Education 64-bit.","pos":[67485,67541]},{"content":"Upgrade existing devices to Windows 10 Education 32-bit.","pos":[67551,67607]},{"content":"Again, you will create the task sequences based on the operating systems that you imported in Step 1.","pos":[67620,67721]},{"content":"For more information about how to create a task sequence, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create a New Task Sequence in the Deployment Workbench<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn759415.aspx#CreateaNewTaskSequenceintheDeploymentWorkbench)</ept>.","pos":[67722,67947]},{"content":"Update the deployment share.","pos":[67988,68016]},{"content":"Updating a deployment share generates the MDT boot images you use to initiate the Windows 10 deployment process.","pos":[68027,68139]},{"content":"You can configure the process to create 32 bit and 64 bit versions of the .iso and .wim files you can use to create bootable media or in Windows Deployment Services.","pos":[68140,68305]},{"content":"For more information about how to update a deployment share, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Update a Deployment Share in the Deployment Workbench<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn759415.aspx#UpdateaDeploymentShareintheDeploymentWorkbench)</ept>.","pos":[68317,68544]},{"content":"Configure Window Deployment Services for MDT","pos":[68579,68623]},{"content":"You can use Windows Deployment Services in conjunction with MDT to automatically initiate boot images on target computers.","pos":[68625,68747]},{"content":"These boot images can be Windows PE images (which you generated in Step 6 in Table 9) or custom images that can deploy operating systems directly to the target computers.","pos":[68748,68918]},{"content":"To configure Windows Deployment Services for MDT","pos":[68925,68973]},{"content":"Set up and configure Windows Deployment Services.","pos":[68978,69027]},{"content":"Windows Deployment Services is a server role available in all Windows Server editions.","pos":[69030,69116]},{"content":"You can enable the Windows Deployment Services server role on a new server or on any server running Windows Server in your institution.","pos":[69117,69252]},{"content":"For more information about how to perform this step, see the following resources:","pos":[69253,69334]},{"content":"Windows Deployment Services overview","pos":[69341,69377]},{"content":"The Windows Deployment Services Help file, included in Windows Deployment Services","pos":[69436,69518]},{"content":"Windows Deployment Services Getting Started Guide for Windows Server 2012","pos":[69524,69597]},{"content":"Add LTI boot images (Windows PE images) to Windows Deployment Services.","pos":[69662,69733]},{"content":"The LTI boot images (.wim files) that you will add to Windows Deployment Services are in the MDT deployment share.","pos":[69736,69850]},{"content":"Locate the .wim files in the Boot subfolder in the deployment share.","pos":[69851,69919]},{"content":"For more information about how to perform this step, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Add LTI Boot Images to Windows Deployment Services<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn759415.aspx#AddLTIBootImagestoWindowsDeploymentServices)</ept>.","pos":[69920,70133]},{"content":"Summary","pos":[70139,70146]},{"content":"Now, Windows Deployment Services is ready to initiate the LTI deployment process in MDT.","pos":[70148,70236]},{"content":"You have set up and configured Windows Deployment Services and added the LTI boot images, which you generated in the previous section, to Windows Deployment Services.","pos":[70237,70403]},{"content":"Now, you’re ready to prepare to manage the devices in your institution.","pos":[70404,70475]},{"content":"Prepare for device management","pos":[70480,70509]},{"content":"Before you deploy Windows 10 in your institution, you must prepare for device management.","pos":[70511,70600]},{"content":"You will deploy Windows 10 in a configuration that complies with your requirements, but you want to help ensure that your deployments remain compliant.","pos":[70601,70752]},{"content":"Select the management method","pos":[70758,70786]},{"content":"If you have only one device to configure, manually configuring that one device is tedious but possible.","pos":[70788,70891]},{"content":"When you have multiple classrooms of devices to configure, however, manually configuring each device becomes overwhelming.","pos":[70892,71014]},{"content":"In addition, manually keeping an identical configuration on each device is virtually impossible as the number of devices in the school increases.","pos":[71015,71160]},{"content":"For a school, there are many ways to manage devices.","pos":[71162,71214]},{"content":"Table 10 lists the methods that this guide describes and recommends.","pos":[71215,71283]},{"content":"Use the information in Table 10 to determine which combination of management methods is right for your institution.","pos":[71284,71399]},{"content":"Table 10.","pos":[71402,71411]},{"content":"School management methods","pos":[71412,71437]},{"content":"Method","pos":[71550,71556]},{"content":"Description","pos":[71579,71590]},{"content":"Group Policy","pos":[71642,71654]},{"content":"Group Policy is an integral part of AD DS and allows you to specify configuration settings for Windows 10 and previous versions of Windows.","pos":[71665,71804]},{"content":"Select this method when you:","pos":[71805,71833]},{"content":"Want to manage institution-owned devices that are domain joined (personally owned devices are typically not domain joined).","pos":[71843,71966]},{"content":"Want more granular control of device and user settings.","pos":[71976,72031]},{"content":"Have an existing AD DS infrastructure.","pos":[72041,72079]},{"content":"Typically manage on-premises devices.","pos":[72089,72126]},{"content":"Can manage a required setting only by using Group Policy.","pos":[72136,72193]},{"content":"The advantages of this method include:","pos":[72206,72244]},{"content":"No cost beyond the AD DS infrastructure.","pos":[72254,72294]},{"content":"A larger number of settings (compared to Intune).","pos":[72304,72353]},{"content":"The disadvantages of this method are:","pos":[72365,72402]},{"content":"Can only manage domain-joined (institution-owned devices).","pos":[72412,72470]},{"content":"Requires an AD DS infrastructure (if the institution does not have AD DS already).","pos":[72480,72562]},{"content":"Typically manages on-premises devices (unless devices connect by using a VPN or DirectAccess).","pos":[72572,72666]},{"content":"Intune","pos":[72713,72719]},{"content":"Intune is a cloud-based management system that allows you to specify configuration settings for Windows 10, previous versions of Windows, and other operating systems (such as iOS or Android).","pos":[72729,72920]},{"content":"Intune is a subscription-based cloud service that integrates with Office 365 and Azure AD.","pos":[72921,73011]},{"content":"Select this method when you:","pos":[73012,73040]},{"content":"Want to manage institution-owned and personal devices (does not require that the device be domain joined).","pos":[73050,73156]},{"content":"Don’t require the level of granular control over device and user settings (compared to Group Policy).","pos":[73166,73267]},{"content":"Don’t have an existing AD DS infrastructure.","pos":[73277,73321]},{"content":"Need to manage devices regardless of where they are (on or off premises).","pos":[73331,73404]},{"content":"Can manage a required setting only by using Intune.","pos":[73414,73465]},{"content":"The advantages of this method are:","pos":[73478,73512]},{"content":"You can manage institution-owned and personal devices.","pos":[73522,73576]},{"content":"It doesn’t require that devices be domain joined.","pos":[73586,73635]},{"content":"It doesn’t require any on-premises infrastructure.","pos":[73645,73695]},{"content":"It can manage devices regardless of their location (on or off premises).","pos":[73705,73777]},{"content":"The disadvantages of this method are:","pos":[73790,73827]},{"content":"Carries an additional cost for subscription.","pos":[73837,73881]},{"content":"Doesn’t have a granular level control over device and user settings (compared to Group Policy).","pos":[73891,73986]},{"content":"Select Microsoft-recommended settings","pos":[74038,74075]},{"content":"Microsoft has several recommended settings for educational institutions.","pos":[74077,74149]},{"content":"Table 11 lists them, provides a brief description of why you need to configure them, and recommends methods for configuring the settings.","pos":[74150,74287]},{"content":"Review the settings in Table 11 and evaluate their relevancy to your institution.","pos":[74288,74369]},{"content":"Use the information to help you determine whether you need to configure the setting and which method you will use to do so.","pos":[74370,74493]},{"content":"At the end, you will have a list of settings that you want to apply to the Windows 10 devices and know which management method you will use to configure the settings.","pos":[74494,74660]},{"content":"Table 11.","pos":[74663,74672]},{"content":"Recommended settings for educational institutions","pos":[74673,74722]},{"content":"Recommendation","pos":[74835,74849]},{"content":"Description","pos":[74872,74883]},{"content":"Use of Microsoft accounts","pos":[74936,74961]},{"content":"You want faculty and students to use only Azure AD accounts for institution-owned devices.","pos":[74971,75061]},{"content":"For these devices, do not use Microsoft accounts or associate a Microsoft account with the Azure AD accounts.","pos":[75062,75171]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">\n**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>Personal devices typically use Microsoft accounts.","pos":[75181,75253]},{"content":"Faculty and students can associate their Microsoft account with their Azure AD account on these devices.","pos":[75254,75358]},{"content":"Group Policy.","pos":[75371,75384]},{"content":"Configure the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Accounts: Block Microsoft accounts<ept id=\"p1\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/jj966262.aspx?f=255&amp;MSPPError=-2147217396)</ept> Group Policy setting to use the Users can’t add Microsoft accounts setting option.","pos":[75387,75607]},{"content":"Intune.","pos":[75620,75627]},{"content":"Enable or disable the camera by using the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Allow Microsoft account<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Allow adding non-Microsoft accounts manually<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, and <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Allow settings synchronization for Microsoft accounts<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> policy settings under the <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>Accounts and Synchronization<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept> section of a <bpt id=\"p5\">**</bpt>Windows 10 General Configuration<ept id=\"p5\">**</ept> policy.","pos":[75630,75929]},{"content":"Restrict local administrator accounts on the devices","pos":[75965,76017]},{"content":"Ensure that only authorized users are local administrators on institution-owne