":[86023,86350]},{"pos":[86352,86520],"content":"For more information about how to configure Intune to manage your apps, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Deploy and configure apps with Microsoft Intune<ept id=\"p1\">](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/intune/)</ept>."},{"content":"Summary","pos":[86526,86533]},{"content":"In this section, you prepared your institution for device management.","pos":[86535,86604]},{"content":"You determined whether you want to use Group Policy or Intune to manage your devices.","pos":[86605,86690]},{"content":"You identified the configuration settings that you want to use to manage your users and devices.","pos":[86691,86787]},{"content":"Finally, you configured the Group Policy and Intune settings in Group Policy and Intune, respectively.","pos":[86788,86890]},{"content":"Deploy Windows 10 to devices","pos":[86895,86923]},{"content":"You’re ready to deploy Windows 10 to faculty and student devices.","pos":[86925,86990]},{"content":"You must complete the steps in this section for each student device in the classrooms as well as for any new student devices you add in the future.","pos":[86991,87138]},{"content":"You can also perform these actions for any device that’s eligible for a Windows 10 upgrade.","pos":[87139,87230]},{"content":"This section discusses deploying Windows 10 to new devices, refreshing Windows 10 on existing devices, and upgrading existing devices that are running eligible versions of Windows 8.1 or Windows to Windows 10.","pos":[87231,87440]},{"content":"Prepare for deployment","pos":[87447,87469]},{"content":"Prior to deployment of Windows 10, ensure that you complete the tasks listed in Table 12.","pos":[87471,87560]},{"content":"Most of these tasks are already complete, but use this step to make sure.","pos":[87561,87634]},{"content":"Table 12.","pos":[87637,87646]},{"content":"Deployment preparation checklist","pos":[87647,87679]},{"content":"Task","pos":[87683,87687]},{"content":"The target devices have sufficient system resources to run Windows 10.","pos":[87715,87785]},{"content":"Identify the necessary devices drivers, and import them to the MDT deployment share.","pos":[87794,87878]},{"content":"Create an MDT application for each Windows Store and Windows desktop app.","pos":[87886,87959]},{"content":"Notify the students and faculty about the deployment.","pos":[87967,88020]},{"content":"Perform the deployment","pos":[88030,88052]},{"content":"Use the Deployment Wizard to deploy Windows 10.","pos":[88054,88101]},{"content":"The LTI deployment process is almost fully automated: You provide only minimal information to the Deployment Wizard at the beginning of the process.","pos":[88102,88250]},{"content":"After the wizard collects the necessary information, the remainder of the process is fully automated.","pos":[88251,88352]},{"pos":[88356,88610],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</ph>To fully automate the LTI deployment process, complete the steps in the “Fully Automated LTI Deployment Scenario” section in the <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Microsoft Deployment Toolkit Samples Guide<ept id=\"p2\">](https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn781089.aspx)</ept>."},{"content":"In most instances, deployments occur without incident.","pos":[88612,88666]},{"content":"Only in rare occasions do deployments experience problems.","pos":[88667,88725]},{"content":"To deploy Windows 10","pos":[88732,88752]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Initiate the LTI deployment process<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[88757,88797]},{"content":"Initiate the LTI deployment process booting over the network (PXE boot) or from local media.","pos":[88798,88890]},{"content":"You selected the method for initiating the LTI deployment process in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Select a method to initiate deployment<ept id=\"p1\">](#select-a-method-to-initiate-deployment)</ept> section earlier in this guide.","pos":[88891,89076]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">*